      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(acp): close ACP runtime on kill and run cross-agent spawns in the target workspace",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nTwo ACP session-lifecycle correctness fixes (separate commits).\n\n### 1. Kill closes ACP runtime\n`killSubagentRun` — the funnel for the subagent kill tool, admin kill, cascade kill, and the HTTP `/sessions/<key>/kill` route — only marked the run aborted and never tore down ACP runtime. For ACP-backed sessions this left the ACPX one-shot record `closed:false` and the OpenClaw `.acp` metadata `state:\"running\"` even though the kill reported success — so a session the operator asked to stop lingered as \"running,\" and a later status/connect could treat the stale-open record as live.\n\nAdds a shared, timeout-guarded `closeAcpSessionRuntime` helper (cancel + close, discarding persisted state and clearing `.acp` metadata; best-effort so a wedged ACP backend cannot make the kill itself hang or fail) and invokes it from the kill path only when the resolved session has `.acp`. Non-ACP kills are unchanged. It is the terminate counterpart to the reset path's existing reuse-oriented cleanup.\n\n### 2. Cross-agent ACP spawns use the target agent workspace\n`resolveSpawnedWorkspaceInheritance` resolved the requester agent's workspace before the target agent's, so a cross-agent ACP spawn (e.g. `claude-code` spawned from `main`) ran in `main`'s workspace instead of the target's. This regressed when requester-workspace inheritance was added for subagent parity, and silently failed the existing acp-spawn cwd tests. Adds an opt-in `preferTargetAgentWorkspace` flag set only by the ACP spawn path; subagent spawns keep inheriting the requester workspace and fall back to the backend default cwd when the target workspace does not exist.\n\n## Verification\n\n- Fix 1 TDD (red→green): kill closes ACP runtime / skips non-ACP / still terminates when ACP cleanup throws; helper unit tests (cancel→close args, no-ACP no-op, cancel-error-still-closes, close-timeout).\n- Fix 2: the pre-existing `acp-spawn` cwd tests (failing since the regression) now pass, plus a new `spawned-context` unit test for the flag.\n- Testbox: `pnpm check:changed` green; `pnpm test:changed` green for the changed-related files. One unrelated file, `doctor.warns-state-directory-is-missing.e2e.test.ts`, fails identically on `origin/main` (pre-existing in-file test-isolation issue — passes in isolation) and is out of scope here.\n- Local: oxfmt, oxlint (0/0), `check:import-cycles` (0), tsgo core + test:src, `pnpm build` (lazy boundary effective, no `INEFFECTIVE_DYNAMIC_IMPORT`).\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
        "branch": "fix/acp-kill-closes-runtime",
